result.execSummary:
The defendant Tanisha Marie Handrich was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Cause Injury/Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (Delta 9 THC), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(2)(a)3.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: In the event probation is revoked, Defendant would be entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.
Prior to re-licensing the defendant is to complete an OWI Assessment.

miscConds.notes: Fine plus Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Same repayment provisions apply as noted above for the Fine.
Defendant to obtain a High School Equivalency Diploma (HSED) during the pendency of probation term.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant will be subject to random urine screens of at least one sample per week.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

Based upon the Restitution Hearing conducted on November 30, 2015, the Court imputed full time earnings capability for Defendant at $10.00 per hour, or $1720.00 monthly, applying the DWD 40 Child Support Guidelines of 29% for three children.  Prorated over a 3 year period due to probation term ordered as to companion Waushara Co Case No. 2015CF000051, the Court ordered restitution in the amount of $17956.80 to be paid in monthly increments of not less than $498.80 ($498.80 per month for 36 months).  ***Cash Bond posted as to companion Waushara Co Case No 2015CF000051 in the amount of $750.00 has been applied to the Restitution owing and disbursed by the Clerk of Circuit Court to the Brian L. Dain Supplemental Needs Trust.***

timeConds.notes: Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges granted.

Commencing with the 2016/2017 and 2017/2018 School Years:  Defendant will be required to present a constructive program to Driver's Education Classes of not less than five high schools each school year.  The presentations to be at least 1/2 hour in duration.  Presentations must include photographs of herself and of the Defendant pre-injury and post-injury; include information regarding her experiences with heroine, drug and alcohol use; and also information about the crash and what happened in the aftermath.  A Court review of her presentation to be conducted no later than 11/01/2016, with members of the victim's family being invited to attend as well.

Case Called @ 1:48 PM: Defendant Tanisha Marie Handrich in court with attorney Greg A Petit.  Scott Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Robert Bellin (State's primary witness for foundation) appears via telephone.  Counsel believes primary issue before the Court today will be Def's ability to pay.  Case law submitted by the State as to contributory negligence.  Ex No 1 marked - 9/10/2015 - out of pocket expenses.  Exhibit entered and received as a summary exhibit under s. 910.06 submission made through the DA office.  $71360.52 agreed upon figure.  Def and counsel confirm she was not insured at time of crash, Victim's insurance has paid some expenses up to a point. Court receives Ex No 1 for evidentiary value and incorporates the entirety of Restitution claimed -  Atty Bellin excused from the hearing.   State is prepared to rest.  Argument by Atty Petit as to Def's ability to pay.  Def sworn in for testimony.  Direct Exam by Atty Petit.  Ex No 2 marked - Financial Disclosure Statement.  Cross Exam by DA Blader.  Re-Direct by Atty Petit.  Re-Cross by DA Blader.  Argument by Atty Petit as to contributory negligence factor/ability to pay.  Argument by DA Blader as to ability to pay - reminds the Court of charges that were dismissed and read in.  Further argument by Atty Petit.  The Court:  Must confront the agreed upon out-of-pocket expenses being requested.  Recites language from the Noll decision from the Court of Appeals and its application to this situation.  Court recognizes the challenges that Def is facing.  Finds earning capacity is currently at $10.00 per hour - earning capacity imputed at $10.00 per hour.  Imputes full time earning capability at $10.00 per hour or $1720.00 monthly as per CSUP guidelines.  Guidelines under DWD 40 of 29% or 3 children, pro rated over 3 yrs of probation as to 15CF-51 or $498.80 per month - 29% of $1720.00 imputed earnings.  Restitution obligation based upon that methodology of $17956.80 fairly assesses her capability of earnings.  Court will amend the JOC.  Ex No 2 withdrawn to allow fiscal situation to remain confidential.

15CF-5 and 15CF-51 - Both Cases Called @ 2:38 PM: Defendant Tanisha Marie Handrich in court with attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per DA:  Resitution will be requested with a bifurcated Restitution Hrg - issues on dollar amount still being worked through.  Atty Zamzow concurs with issues on Restitution.  15CF51:  Court entertains waiver of pre-lim hrg in its entirety. Court accepts knowing and voluntary waiver of pre-lim hearing.  Def BOT w/PC Finding.  INFO Filed.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Def will plead to Ct 1 of INFO - Fel Bump.  Def also intends to enter plea to amended charge in Ct 1 of 15CF-5.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty as to each case.  Terms of bifurcated SEH explained.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained.  Chapter 950 compliance addressed - many victims present today.  15CF-5:  Accepts State's Motion to amend to Op MV on Highway w/detectable RCS Causing Injury contrary to s. 346.63(2)(a)3 - 15CF-5 Plea Amended Ct 1:  NC  15CF-51 Plea Ct 1 INFO (Fel BJump):  NC  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  15CF-5 Cts 2 and 3 DRI.  15CF-51 Ct 2 DRI.  Photographs submitted by the State for Court's review - record to reflect also that the Court had previously reviewed all victim submissions prior to today's hearing. Court reviews photographs.  Victim Robin Wing (Def's Fiance) makes statement to the Court.  Court reviews her picture boards.  Marjorie Dain (Victim's daughter) makes statement to the Court.  Randy Dain (Def's Brother) makes statement to the Court.  Brief recess - off record.  Back of Record at 3:25 PM:  Lavonne Handrich (Def's Grandmother) makes statement ot the Court.   Argument by DA as to penalty - no less than 200 days WCJ cond'l time and strenuously against any expungement argument as to Class H felony.  Court reviews Toxicology Report and photos of tractor from accident scene.  Def's FB/social media messages also reviewed by the Court.  CCAP Citation information reviewed by the Court - 3 tickets.  Believes Def would be entitled to 1 day TS credit.   Argument by Atty Zamzow - argues for guideline Co Jail of 30 days.  Also argues as to expugement.  Statement by Def:  Written statement provided for Court's review.  Def does not believe she can read statement on her own.  Court reads her Statement into the record.  The Court:  15CF-5:  1 yr WCJ - I/S - S/W - 1 yr. Conditions:  4 mos WCJ - 4/1/2016 Report Date, GT Credit, AODA and any follow thru as recommended; Ab Sob; Bar Prohibition; No illegal RX, Random urinalysis 1 per week; $600 fine inclusive of costs; 18 mos DL rev; OWI assessment; IID requirement for 18 mos; no opportunity to expunge this conviction. 15CF-51: S/W - 3 yrs probation - concurrent to 15CF-5. Conditions:  75 days WCJ - served consecutive to 15CF-5 - w/o GT credit, served in two parts of 38 and 37 days stints - 11/20/2016 to 12/28/2016 - first portion of sentence 38 days with good time encompassing Thanksgiving and Christmas holidays. 2nd Period 11/20/2017 to 12/27/2017 Thanksgiving and Xmas Holiday as well taken away - 75 days total; conditions of probation same as ordered in 15CF-5 - Community Service as per the following:  2016/17 School Year and 2017/18 School Year - one half hour presentation that will be made to driver's education classes at 5 high schools each year. Presentation to Include photographs of herself and pre-post photographs of Def, include her experience with heroine use and alcohol use, information about the crash and what happened in the aftermath.  Prior to first presentation there will be a  return to court to view presentation with Def's family members being invited.  To be a constructive and positive process and a practice run prior to giving presentation to school.  Review with the Court to take place on a date no later than 11/1/2016.  Restitution will be paid in an amount TBT and a payment schedule TBT; Complete HSED; Court Costs plus Surcharge; Sample to be provided tomorrow due to late hour of the day; Expungement process of DNA Sample explained thru DOJ; Def may expunge if all presentations completed and successful discharge from supervision - Expungement must be earned however.  Appeal Rights Given.  1 day TS credit as to 15CF-5.  Bond posted to be held by COC pending resolution of next hearing on restitution.  State withdraws motion to forfeit bond filed 4/22/2015.  Restitution Hrg Scheduled - NOH Given.  Restitution hearing scheduled for November 3, 2015 at 10:00 am.
